Response to
Episode 8 - "Sisters of the Sun"
@-------------------------------------------------
- Different cultures have different stories about stars and the meanings behind them. Most common one I believe are the 12 constellations representing the 12 zodiac signs for every 30 or so days of the year.
- The talk about sister stars made me research about what are our sun's sister stars and I found out that a sister star has been found. It is a star called HD 162826 located 110 light years away in the constellation Hercules. It cannot be seen by the naked eye but can be seen with low-power binoculars. Source: https://www.space.com/25881-sun-sister-star-found-hd162826.html.
- I really hope that by the time the sun turns into a red star and wants to swallow earth, humans will develop the technology to survive this event.
- All of this scientific information provided to use about the reasons for the events that occur in space completely counter the religious ideas that some cultures talk about.
